column14:
Spring 2021–Spring 2025 headcounts by major vs. pre-major show overall stability (total 659 ? 624), with Arts & Social Sciences edging up (210 ? 223) on gains in Art Education (pre-majors 22 ? 38, total 35 ? 55) and a sharp 2025 jump in History (total 84 ? 87, with the major line rising). Education is mixed (total 276 ? 243; Elementary Education–English total 129 ? 106 while History emphasis rises 32 ? 43), Health & Rehabilitation Sciences holds steady (83–101) as Physical Education stays near the low-80s and Dance Ed grows (17 ? 18), and Engineering/Science & Tech softens (73 ? 57), with small declines in Math (21 ? 19) and Tech & Engineering Ed K-12 flat (~16).

Abbreviations: BA = Bachelor of Arts; BS-Teach = Bachelor of Science with teacher certification track; MA/MS = Master of Arts/Science; GRADCERT = graduate certificate; OHE = internal program/organization code; CIP = Classification of Instructional Programs code; Pre-major = students admitted to the school/area but not yet into the full major.
